SIMPLE: improvement
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Improvement
<hw>Im*prove"ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
act of improving; advancement or growth; promotion in desirable
qualities; progress toward what is better; melioration; <as>as, the
<ex>improvement</ex> of the mind, of land, roads, etc.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I look upon your city as the best place of
<qex>improvement</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Exercise is the chief source of <qex>improvement</qex> in all our
faculties.</q> <rj><qau>Blair.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The act of making profitable use or application of
anything, or the state of being profitably employed; a turning to good
account; practical application, as of a doctrine, principle, or theory,
stated in a discourse.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A good <xex>improvement</xex> of his
reason.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>S. Clarke.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I shall make some <qex>improvement</qex> of this doctrine.</q>
<rj><qau>Tillotson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The state of being improved; betterment; advance;
also, that which is improved; <as>as, the new edition is an
<ex>improvement</ex> on the old</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The parts of Sinon, Camilla, and some few others, are
<qex>improvements</qex> on the Greek poet.</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Increase; growth; progress; advance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>There is a design of publishing the history of architecture, with
its several <qex>improvements</qex> and decays.</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Those vices which more particularly receive <qex>improvement</qex>
by prosperity.</q> <rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <pluf>pl.</pluf> <def>Valuable additions or betterments,
as buildings, clearings, drains, fences, etc., on land or premises;
<as>as, to convey the land together with all
<ex>improvements</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>6.</sn> <fld>(Patent Laws)</fld> <def>A useful addition to, or
modification of, a machine, manufacture, or composition.</def>
<rj><au>Kent.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Improver</ent>⟦br⟧
